# Minclips — Naming (`mcvc_` / `mcvw_`) · Shots 模块

**Primary source**: **`minclips-always.mdc`** (`alwaysApply: true`) defines **`mcvc_`** vs **`mcvw_`**. This file adds **Shots-facing examples** only; do not contradict the global rule.

## Type names

- Prefer **`MCC`** + domain + role: **`MCCShotsController`**, **`MCCShotsView`**, **`MCCShotsListPageController`**.
- There is **no** **`MCCShotController`** in the repo — use **`MCCShotsController`** (plural **Shots**).

## Quick reference

| Location | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| **`MCCShotsController`** own properties / private methods | **`mcvc_`** | `mcvc_selectedTagIndex`, `mcvc_loadTags()` |
| **`MCCShotsView`** (and Cells under Shots) members | **`mcvw_`** | `mcvw_tagCollection`, `mcvw_setupPagingView(delegate:)` |
| From **`MCCShotsController`**, access root view | **`contentView.mcvw_…`** | `contentView.mcvw_applyPagingTagReload(...)` |
| Child controller you create (e.g. list page) fields you set from parent | **`mcvc_`** on the child | `list.mcvc_labelItem = …`, `list.mcvc_index = …` |

## Anti-patterns

- **`contentView.mcvc_*`** for view members — wrong; use **`mcvw_`** on the View type.
- **`mcvw_`** prefix on **`MCCShotsController`** for its own state — wrong; use **`mcvc_`**.
- Module-specific extra prefixes (**`mcsv_`**, etc.) for new code — avoid; rely on type names (**`MCPViewControllerInitProtocol`** lifecycle names like **`mcvc_bind`** stay without the extra `mc` segment by design).

## Protocol & system APIs

- **`override`** lifecycle / **`MCPViewControllerInitProtocol`** hooks keep their **fixed names** (**`mcvc_bind`**, **`mcvc_loadData`**) — no **`mcvc_loadDataTags`** replacing the protocol method.
- **`UICollectionViewDelegate` / `JXPagingViewDelegate`** methods stay **Apple signatures**; only **your** helpers use **`mcvc_*`**.
